race.comment: BIG SEXY (11) is the one with upside that can take this out. The first up win at Hamilton was very good as favourite before going under as favourite at Bendigo when settling outside the leader on a day it was beneficial to be on the rails. Drawn very wide but is the horse that can elevate significantly. DUBAI WATCH (8) is one that can run well at each-way odds, finding the line strongly in the Geelong qualifier last time out. Up to a mile suits and he can get the right run in the three-wide with cover line. GUERITE (6) beat BIG SEXY in the Bendigo lead-up, given a great ride to do so. She's progressive herself and should relish this trip. CELSIUS STAR (1) was third at Bendigo with the big weight and has to have each-way claims again.
